<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057071-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 7 and c = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>3.9</li><li>61.0</li><li>29.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}={49}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}-{49}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{15}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{15}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3.8729833462074}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3.9}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{7}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{61.04497562814}\approx{61}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{7}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{28.95502437186}\approx{29}</m></p>

</solution>
